22	//! Wellformedness checks operating on the parser AST.
23	//!
24	//! Port of `Theory.Tools.Wellformedness` from
25	//! `lib/theory/src/Theory/Tools/Wellformedness.hs`. This implementation
26	//! works directly on the surface syntax tree because we don't yet have
27	//! a typed `Theory` AST. As a consequence:
28	//!
29	//! - Checks that need term-level sort inference (e.g. `Nat Sorts`) work
30	//!   over the parser's [`SortHint`] / sigil annotations rather than a
31	//!   full sort assignment.
32	//! - Checks that depend on Maude (`Variants`, `Rule has no variants`)
33	//!   are not implemented yet.
34	//! - The error messages we emit may not match Tamarin's word-for-word,
35	//!   but the *topic strings* (the underlined headers) match exactly so
36	//!   the fixture runner can compare topic sets.
37	//!
38	//! Each public `check_*` function corresponds to a Haskell `*Report`
39	//! function. The umbrella entry point is [`check_theory`].
